title: Standardize one file
text: vignette shows typical workflow standardize camera trap file Snapshot Safari.
code: library(standardizeSnapshot)

title: Standardize one file
text: optional recommended step. want print messages console, also save file, can use logger. function create_logger allows create file specified location setup logging:
code: logfile <- file.path(tempdir(), "log", "logger.log") logfile #> [1] "/tmp/Rtmp2TFAKG/log/logger.log"  logger <- create_logger(my_logfile = logfile,                          console = FALSE) #> Create logger /tmp/Rtmp2TFAKG/log/logger.log

title: Standardize one file
text: First, need read data. , read file previously written /tmp/Rtmp2TFAKG/data_in (shown). dataframe represents Digikam-like data: NB: file digikam dataset included package. can reproduce following results using:
code: in_folder <- file.path(tempdir(), "data_in") in_folder #> [1] "/tmp/Rtmp2TFAKG/data_in"  df <- read.csv(file.path(in_folder,  "digikam.csv")) head(df, 3) #>   X Station   Species DateTimeOriginal       Date     Time delta.time.secs #> 1 1     G03 porcupine  2018-06-28 8:56 2018-06-28 17:38:42               0 #> 2 2     D06      kudu 2018-06-25 16:13 2018-06-25  7:18:05               0 #> 3 3     E06 springbok 2018-06-29 18:33 2018-06-29  0:53:56          353978 #>   delta.time.mins delta.time.hours delta.time.days            Directory #> 1             0.0              0.0             0.0 E:/MOK/MOK_Roll1/G03 #> 2             0.0              0.0             0.0 E:/MOK/MOK_Roll1/D06 #> 3          5899.6             98.3             4.1 E:/MOK/MOK_Roll1/E06 #>       FileName EXIF.Model EXIF.Make metadata_Species metadata_Number #> 1 I_00006a.JPG         E3 CUDDEBACK        porcupine               1 #> 2 I_00003a.JPG         E3 CUDDEBACK             kudu               1 #> 3 I__00013.JPG         E3 CUDDEBACK        springbok               1 #>   metadata_Behaviour metadata_Sex n_images metadata_young_present #> 1               <NA>         <NA>        1                   <NA> #> 2             Moving       Female        1                   <NA> #> 3             Moving         <NA>        1                   <NA> #>   metadata_Numberofindividuals #> 1                           NA #> 2                           NA #> 3                           NA #>                                                                     HierarchicalSubject #> 1                                          Species, Species|porcupine, Number|1, Number #> 2 Species|kudu, Behaviour, Sex|Female, Number|1, Behaviour|Moving, Species, Number, Sex #> 3             Number, Behaviour|Moving, Species, Number|1, Species|springbok, Behaviour data(digikam) df <- digikam

title: Standardize one file
text: , standardize file. function standardize_snapshot_df allows standardize single dataframe. function number options, ones mandatory : df: dataframe standardize standard_df: reference dataframe telling function rename columns. , use built-dataset standard. , also use 2 optional arguments: locationID_digikam: location code, useful data processed Digikam: indeed, location (reserve) determined dataframe alone. logger: logger created create_logger. setup logger, can ignore argument. default, function displays head first 8 columns file along numerous messages.
code: std_df <- standardize_snapshot_df(df = df,                                    standard_df = standard,                                   locationID_digikam = "MOK",                                   logger = logger) #> Initial file: 22 columns, 100 rows. #> Standardizing columns #> Match found in column names: renaming column metadata_Numberofindividuals into metadata_NumberOfIndividuals #> Standardizing dates/times #> Getting location code for Digikam data #> Fill capture info #> Cleaning location/camera, species and columns values #> Final file: 27 columns, 100 rows. Here is a sneak peek: #> locationID   cameraID    season  roll    eventID snapshotName    eventDate   eventTime #> MOK  MOK_A09 NA  1   MOK_A09#1#1 giraffe 2018-07-08  12:15:34 #> MOK  MOK_A09 NA  1   MOK_A09#1#2 springbok   2018-08-26  10:45:55 #> MOK  MOK_A09 NA  1   MOK_A09#1#3 unresolvable    2018-09-02  18:11:28 #> MOK  MOK_B07 NA  1   MOK_B07#1#1 zebraburchells  2018-06-28  07:49:42 #> MOK  MOK_B07 NA  1   MOK_B07#1#2 gemsbok 2018-08-19  09:11:55

title: Standardize one file
text: last step write standardized file destination. , use function write_standardized_df. function 2 mandatory arguments: df: file write : folder file copied. , also use logger argument (data standardization step). file now written destination. can check logger filled:
code: out_folder <- file.path(tempdir(), "data_out") # the folder in which to copy the file out_folder #> [1] "/tmp/Rtmp2TFAKG/data_out"  write_standardized_df(df = std_df,                       to = out_folder,                       logger = logger) #> Creating folder /tmp/Rtmp2TFAKG/data_out #> Writing file /tmp/Rtmp2TFAKG/data_out/MOK_SNA_R1.csv --- list.files(out_folder) #> [1] "MOK_SNA_R1.csv" list.files(file.path(tempdir(), "log")) #> [1] "logger.log" readLines(logfile) #>  [1] "INFO  [2024-04-13 18:02:56] Create logger /tmp/Rtmp2TFAKG/log/logger.log"                                                                #>  [2] "INFO  [2024-04-13 18:02:56] Initial file: 22 columns, 100 rows."                                                                         #>  [3] "INFO  [2024-04-13 18:02:56] Standardizing columns"                                                                                       #>  [4] "INFO  [2024-04-13 18:02:57] Match found in column names: renaming column metadata_Numberofindividuals into metadata_NumberOfIndividuals" #>  [5] "INFO  [2024-04-13 18:02:57] Standardizing dates/times"                                                                                   #>  [6] "INFO  [2024-04-13 18:02:57] Getting location code for Digikam data"                                                                      #>  [7] "INFO  [2024-04-13 18:02:57] Fill capture info"                                                                                           #>  [8] "INFO  [2024-04-13 18:02:57] Cleaning location/camera, species and columns values"                                                        #>  [9] "INFO  [2024-04-13 18:02:57] Final file: 27 columns, 100 rows. Here is a sneak peek:"                                                     #> [10] "locationID\tcameraID\tseason\troll\teventID\tsnapshotName\teventDate\teventTime"                                                         #> [11] "MOK\tMOK_A09\tNA\t1\tMOK_A09#1#1\tgiraffe\t2018-07-08\t12:15:34"                                                                         #> [12] "MOK\tMOK_A09\tNA\t1\tMOK_A09#1#2\tspringbok\t2018-08-26\t10:45:55"                                                                       #> [13] "MOK\tMOK_A09\tNA\t1\tMOK_A09#1#3\tunresolvable\t2018-09-02\t18:11:28"                                                                    #> [14] "MOK\tMOK_B07\tNA\t1\tMOK_B07#1#1\tzebraburchells\t2018-06-28\t07:49:42"                                                                  #> [15] "MOK\tMOK_B07\tNA\t1\tMOK_B07#1#2\tgemsbok\t2018-08-19\t09:11:55"                                                                         #> [16] ""                                                                                                                                        #> [17] "INFO  [2024-04-13 18:02:57] Creating folder /tmp/Rtmp2TFAKG/data_out"                                                                    #> [18] "INFO  [2024-04-13 18:02:57] Writing file /tmp/Rtmp2TFAKG/data_out/MOK_SNA_R1.csv ---"

title: Standardize multiple files
text: vignette shows typical workflow standardize multiple camera trap files Snapshot Safari.
code: library(standardizeSnapshot)

title: Standardize multiple files
text: optional recommended step. want print messages console, also save file, can use logger. function create_logger allows create file specified location setup logging:
code: logfile <- file.path(tempdir(), "log", "logger.log") # create the logfile logfile #> [1] "/tmp/Rtmpzpfy7V/log/logger.log"  logger <- create_logger(my_logfile = logfile,                          console = FALSE) #> Create logger /tmp/Rtmpzpfy7V/log/logger.log

title: Standardize multiple files

Therefore, better copy standardized results list overwrite older results save space. can reproduce following results using:

title: Standardize multiple files

title: Standardize and clean Snapshot data
text: Snapshot Safari data comes different standards, following method used classify pictures (Zooniverse, TrapTagger Digikam). R package allows standardize data sources unique file format. Warning: outputs thoroughly checked (particular camera IDs).

title: Standardize and clean Snapshot data
text: can install package using following commands R console (NB: need internet connection):
code: install.packages("devtools") # if devtools is not installed already library(devtools) devtools::install_github("https://github.com/SnapshotSafari/standard-merge",                          build_vignettes = TRUE)

title: Standardize and clean Snapshot data
text: package website lists documentation functions reference section. Two articles website also show typical workflow package standardize one several file(s). NB: can also read functions documentation file standardizeSnapshot_xx.pdf root directory view articles R vignette("standardize-file") vignette("standardize-files").

title: Standardize and clean Snapshot data

title: Clean cameras — clean_cameras
text: data: add location prefix. TrapTagger data: location code KHO: remove dash camera name (e.g KHO_E_A01 -> KHO_EA01) location code SAM: remove dash camera name (e.g SAM_B_A01 -> SAM_BA01) location code SAM: remove dash camera name (e.g TSW_L_A01 -> TSW_LA01) location code PLN: replace leading PIL_ PLN (e.g PIL_A01 -> PLN_A01) Zooniverse data: location code KHO, replace KHOG E  KHOL M cameras (add location prefix). location code DHP, remove leading D cameras  (add location prefix). location code OVE, remove leading O cameras  (add location prefix).

title: Clean cameras — clean_cameras
code: cameras <- c("KHO_E_A01", "OCO2") locations <- c("KHO", "OVE") classifiers <- c("traptagger", "zooniverse") clean_cameras(cameras, locations, classifiers) #> [1] "KHO_EA01" "OVE_CO2"

title: Standardize dataframe — standardize_snapshot_df
text: standardized dataframe: columns specified standard_df$new, dates times standardized columns regarding information capture filled. Species names (snapshotName) cameraID locationID standardized (see details). Columns order provided standard_df$new rows ordered ascending camera, date time.

title: Standardize dataframe — standardize_snapshot_df
text: Dates times standardized YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS. columns locationID, cameraID, roll, capture season (classifier zooniverse) filled meaningful information. Species names (snapshotName) standardized match existing, known species names. column locationID: location code DHP replaced OVE corresponding camera code starts 'O'. location code KGA replaced KHO corresponding camera code starts 'KHO'. column cameraID: TrapTagger data: remove leading location code part data (eg location ATH, change cameras ATH_A01 -> A01). Also, location code KHO, SAM TSW: remove dash camera name (e.g KHO_E_A01 -> EA01) Zooniverse data: location code KHO, replace KHOG E  KHOL M cameras. location code DHP, remove leading D cameraID. location code OVE, remove leading O cameraID. column eventID: event ID formatted season#cam_site#roll#event_no.

what: Standardize a list of dataframes — standardize_snapshot_list
title: Standardize a list of dataframes — standardize_snapshot_list
text: Standardizes list dataframes Snapshot standard.

title: Standardize a list of dataframes — standardize_snapshot_list
code: standardize_snapshot_list(   df_list,   standard_df,   classifier,   logger = NA,   verbose = TRUE )

title: Standardize a list of dataframes — standardize_snapshot_list
text: df_list list dataframes. standard_df standard dataframe match column names new standard. dataframe >= 2 columns, one must named zooniverse, digikam traptagger another one must named new. classifier Optional character vector characters classifier. logger log4r logger object want logging (can created create_logger), else NA. verbose lot details given executing function?

title: Standardize a list of dataframes — standardize_snapshot_list
text: list standardized dataframes: columns specified standard_df$new, dates times standardized columns regarding information capture filled. Species names (snapshotName) cameraID locationID standardized (see details). Columns order provided standard_df$new rows ordered ascending camera, date time.

title: Standardize a list of dataframes — standardize_snapshot_list
text: Dates times standardized YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS. columns locationID, cameraID, roll, capture season (classifier zooniverse) filled meaningful information. Species names (snapshotName) standardized match existing, known species names. column locationID: location code DHP replaced OVE corresponding camera code starts 'O'. location code KGA replaced KHO corresponding camera code starts 'KHO'. column cameraID: TrapTagger data: remove leading location code part data (eg location ATH, change cameras ATH_A01 -> A01). Also, location code KHO, SAM TSW: remove dash camera name (e.g KHO_E_A01 -> EA01) Zooniverse data: location code KHO, replace KHOG E  KHOL M cameras. location code DHP, remove leading D cameraID. location code OVE, remove leading O cameraID. column eventID: event ID formatted season#cam_site#roll#event_no.

title: Standardize a list of dataframes — standardize_snapshot_list
